content.sentence: Problem Statement
content.parserSentence: Problem Statement

content.sentence: As the head of information systems for Wylie College you are tasked with developing a new student registration system.
content.parserSentence: As the head of information systems for Wylie College you are tasked with developing a new student registration system.

content.sentence: The college would like a new client-server system to replace its much older system developed around mainframe technology.
content.parserSentence: The college would like a new client-server system to replace its much older system developed around mainframe technology.

content.sentence: The new system will allow students to register for courses and view report cards from personal computers attached to the campus LAN.
content.parserSentence: The new system will allow students to register for courses and view report cards from personal computers attached to the campus LAN.

content.sentence: Professors will be able to access the system to sign up to teach courses as well as record grades.
content.parserSentence: Professors will be able to access the system to sign up to teach courses as well as record grades.

content.sentence: Due to a decrease in federal funding, the college cannot afford to replace the entire system at once.
content.parserSentence: Due to a decrease in federal funding, the college cannot afford to replace the entire system at once.

content.sentence: The college will keep the existing course catalog database where all course information is maintained.
content.parserSentence: The college will keep the existing course catalog database where all course information is maintained.

content.sentence: This database is an Ingres relational database running on a DEC VAX.
content.parserSentence: This database is an Ingres relational database running on a DEC VAX.

content.sentence: Fortunately the college has invested in an open SQL interface that allows access to this database from college’s Unix servers.
content.parserSentence: Fortunately the college has invested in an open SQL interface that allows access to this database from college’s Unix servers.

content.sentence: The legacy system performance is rather poor, so the new system must ensure that access to the data on the legacy system occurs in a timely manner.
content.parserSentence: The legacy system performance is rather poor, so the new system must ensure that access to the data on the legacy system occurs in a timely manner.

content.sentence: The new system will access course information from the legacy database but will not update it.
content.parserSentence: The new system will access course information from the legacy database but will not update it.

content.sentence: The registrar’s office will continue to maintain course information through another system.
content.parserSentence: The registrar’s office will continue to maintain course information through another system.

content.sentence: At the beginning of each semester, students may request a course catalogue containing a list of course offerings for the semester.
content.parserSentence: At the beginning of each semester, students may request a course catalogue containing a list of course offerings for the semester.

content.sentence: Information about each course, such as professor, department, and prerequisites, will be included to help students make informed decisions.
content.parserSentence: Information about each course, such as professor, department, and prerequisites, will be included to help students make informed decisions.

content.sentence: The new system will allow students to select four course offerings for the coming semester.
content.parserSentence: The new system will allow students to select four course offerings for the coming semester.

content.sentence: In addition, each student will indicate two alternative choices in case the student cannot be assigned to a primary selection.
content.parserSentence: In addition, each student will indicate two alternative choices in case the student cannot be assigned to a primary selection.

content.sentence: Course offerings will have a maximum of ten students and a minimum of three students.
content.parserSentence: Course offerings will have a maximum of ten students and a minimum of three students.

content.sentence: A course offering with fewer than three students will be canceled.
content.parserSentence: A course offering with fewer than three students will be canceled.

content.sentence: For each semester, there is a period of time that students can change their schedule.
content.parserSentence: For each semester, there is a period of time that students can change their schedule.

content.sentence: Students must be able to access the system during this time to add or drop courses.
content.parserSentence: Students must be able to access the system during this time to add or drop courses.

content.sentence: Once the registration process is completed for a student, the registration system sends information to the billing system so the student can be billed for the semester.
content.parserSentence: Once the registration process is completed for a student, the registration system sends information to the billing system so the student can be billed for the semester.

content.sentence: If a course fills up during the actual registration process, the student must be notified of the change before submitting the schedule for processing.
content.parserSentence: If a course fills up during the actual registration process, the student must be notified of the change before submitting the schedule for processing.

content.sentence: At the end of the semester, the student will be able to access the system to view an electronic report card.
content.parserSentence: At the end of the semester, the student will be able to access the system to view an electronic report card.

content.sentence: Since student grades are sensitive information, the system must employ extra security measures to prevent unauthorized access.
content.parserSentence: Since student grades are sensitive information, the system must employ extra security measures to prevent unauthorized access.

content.sentence: Professors must be able to access the on-line system to indicate which courses they will be teaching.
content.parserSentence: Professors must be able to access the on-line system to indicate which courses they will be teaching.

content.sentence: They will also need to see which students signed up for their course offerings.
content.parserSentence: They will also need to see which students signed up for their course offerings.

content.sentence: In addition, the professors will be able to record the grades for the students in each class.

content.sentence: Brief Description
content.parserSentence: Brief Description

content.sentence: This use case allows a Registrar to close the registration process.
content.parserSentence: This use case allows a Registrar to close the registration process.

content.sentence: Course offerings that do not have enough students are cancelled.
content.parserSentence: Course offerings that do not have enough students are cancelled.

content.sentence: Course offerings must have a minimum of three students in them.
content.parserSentence: Course offerings must have a minimum of three students in them.

content.parserSentence: Flow of Events

content.sentence: Basic Flow
content.parserSentence: Basic Flow

content.sentence: This use case starts when the Registrar requests that the system close registration.
content.parserSentence: This use case starts when the Registrar requests that the system close registration.

content.sentence: 1) 	The system checks to see if registration is in progress.
content.parserSentence: The system checks to see if registration is in progress.

content.sentence: If it is, then a message is displayed to the Registrar, and the use case terminates.
content.parserSentence: If it is, then a message is displayed to the Registrar, and the use case terminates.

content.sentence: The Close Registration processing cannot be performed if registration is in progress.
content.parserSentence: The Close Registration processing cannot be performed if registration is in progress.

content.sentence: 2) For each course offering, the system checks if a professor has signed up to teach the course offering and at least three students have registered.
content.parserSentence: For each course offering, the system checks if a professor has signed up to teach the course offering and at least three students have registered.

content.sentence: If so, the system commits the course offering for each schedule that contains it.
content.comments: It is a pronomial back to course offering.
content.parserSentence: If so, the system commits the course offering for each schedule that contains it.

content.sentence: 3) For each schedule, the system levels the schedule: if the schedule does not have the maximum number of primary courses selected, the system attempts to select alternates from the schedule’s list of alternates.
content.parserSentence: For each schedule, the system levels the schedule: if the schedule does not have the maximum number of primary courses selected, the system attempts to select alternates from the schedule’s list of alternates.

content.sentence: The first available alternate course offerings will be selected.
content.parserSentence: The first available alternate course offerings will be selected.

content.sentence: If no alternates are available, then no substitution will be made.
content.comments: can probably argue that there's no access control.  However, the system had to read data to make these decisions.
content.parserSentence: If no alternates are available, then no substitution will be made.

content.sentence: 4) For each course offering, the system closes all course offerings.
content.parserSentence: For each course offering, the system closes all course offerings.

content.sentence: If the course offerings do not have at least three students at this point (some may have been added as a result of leveling), then the system cancels the course offering.
content.parserSentence: If the course offerings do not have at least three students at this point (some may have been added as a result of leveling), then the system cancels the course offering.

content.sentence: The system cancels the course offering for each schedule that contains it.
content.parserSentence: The system cancels the course offering for each schedule that contains it.

content.sentence: 5) The system calculates the tuition owed by each student for his current semester schedule and sends a transaction to the Billing System.
content.parserSentence: The system calculates the tuition owed by each student for his current semester schedule and sends a transaction to the Billing System.

content.sentence: The Billing System will send the bill to the students, which will include a copy of their final schedule.
content.comments: Billing system sending the bill is outside the scope of this system.  however, the billing system needs to get the final schedule from this one.
content.parserSentence: The Billing System will send the bill to the students, which will include a copy of their final schedule.
